// ============================================================
// schema.prisma  (root — kept for tooling compat)
//
// With Prisma's `prismaSchemaFolder` preview feature enabled
// in base.prisma, the CLI reads ALL *.prisma files inside
// the `prisma/schemas/` folder and merges them automatically.
//
// File layout:
//   prisma/
//   ├── schema.prisma          ← this file (entry point / legacy compat)
//   └── schemas/
//       ├── base.prisma        ← generator + datasource
//       ├── user.prisma        ← User model + UserRole enum
//       └── (future domains)   ← product.prisma, order.prisma, …
//
// To add a new domain:
//   1. Create prisma/schemas/<domain>.prisma
//   2. Define models + enums scoped to that domain
//   3. Run `npx prisma generate` — no changes needed here
//
// Migration workflow:
//   npx prisma migrate dev --name <description>
//   npx prisma migrate deploy   (CI/CD / production)
//   npx prisma db seed          (seed data)
// ============================================================

// Re-export everything from the schemas/ folder.
// Prisma CLI resolves all sibling *.prisma files automatically
// when `prismaSchemaFolder` feature is active.

// NOTE: Do NOT define models or enums here — keep them in
// prisma/schemas/*.prisma files for clean domain separation.
